// Sample data for the trash collection app
export const sampleUser = {
  id: 1,
  name: 'John Doe',
  email: 'john.doe@example.com',
  role: 'admin',
  avatar: '/api/placeholder/40/40'
};

export const collections = [
  {
    id: 1,
    address: '123 Main St',
    scheduledDate: '2025-06-15',
    status: 'pending',
    type: 'regular',
    priority: 'normal',
    notes: 'Regular weekly pickup'
  },
  {
    id: 2,
    address: '456 Oak Ave',
    scheduledDate: '2025-06-14',
    status: 'completed',
    type: 'recycling',
    priority: 'normal',
    notes: 'Recycling collection'

  {
    id: 3,
    address: '789 Pine Rd',
    scheduledDate: '2025-06-16',
    status: 'in-progress',
    type: 'bulk',
    priority: 'high',
    notes: 'Large furniture items'
  },
  {
    id: 4,
    address: '321 Elm St',
    scheduledDate: '2025-06-13',
    status: 'missed',
    type: 'regular',
    priority: 'normal',

  {
    id: 5,
    address: '654 Maple Dr',
    scheduledDate: '2025-06-17',
    status: 'pending',
    type: 'hazardous',
    priority: 'high',
    notes: 'Hazardous waste disposal'

];

export const payments = [
  {
    id: 1,

    id: 2,

  {
    id: 3,
    customerName: 'Mike Wilson',
    address: '789 Pine Rd',
    amount: 45.00,
    dueDate: '2025-06-15',
    status: 'overdue',
    paymentDate: null,
    method: null

  {
    id: 4,
    customerName: 'Emily Brown',
    address: '321 Elm St',
    amount: 25.00,
    dueDate: '2025-06-25',

  {
    id: 5,
    customerName: 'David Lee',
    address: '654 Maple Dr',
    amount: 35.00,
    dueDate: '2025-06-18',
    status: 'pending',
    paymentDate: null,
    method: null
  }
];

export const dashboardStats = {
  totalCollections: collections.length,
  completedToday: collections.filter(c => c.status === 'completed' && c.scheduledDate === '2025-06-12').length,
  pendingCollections: collections.filter(c => c.status === 'pending').length,
  totalRevenue: payments.reduce((sum, p) => p.status === 'paid' ? sum + p.amount : sum, 0),
  overduePayments: payments.filter(p => p.status === 'overdue').length,
  activeRoutes: 3
};

export const routes = [
  {
    id: 1,
    name: 'Route A - Downtown',
    driver: 'Mike Johnson',
    truck: 'Truck #101',
    status: 'active',
    stops: 15,
    completedStops: 8,
    estimatedCompletion: '14:30'
  },
  {
    id: 2,
    name: 'Route B - Suburbs',
    driver: 'Sarah Davis',
    truck: 'Truck #102',
    status: 'active',
    stops: 22,

    truck: 'Truck #103',

export const notifications = [
